WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.000
narrator: OctraVPN — a self-hosted, chain-anchored tailnet.

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:13.000
narrator: stock Tailscale clients, our control plane, real WireGuard.

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:21.000
narrator: operators deploy, settle, and audit on the Octra chain.

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:30.000
narrator: act one — the chain side. A contract handles every session.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:39.000
narrator: register, settle, claim, slash — each step is a recorded tx.

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:48.000
narrator: an overclaim is rejected — the bond enforces honest payout.

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:57.000
narrator: act two — the oct:// portal. URLs resolve against chain state.

00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:06.000
narrator: policy and sealed assets live on-chain, fetched on demand.

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:15.000
narrator: act three — the headscale-rs control plane on Tailscale wire.

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:24.000
narrator: users, preauth keys, and nodes — the day-2 admin surface.

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:33.000
narrator: act four — the data plane. Three peers, full-mesh WireGuard.

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:42.000
narrator: peer-to-peer ping and HTTP rides direct UDP where it can.

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:51.000
narrator: DERP relays catch the rest — the operator ships the sidecar.

00:01:51.000 --> 00:02:00.000
narrator: act five — observability. Prometheus, JSON series, health.

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:09.000
narrator: the analytics indexer scans the audit log per minute.

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:18.000
narrator: act six — audit. An HMAC-chained log plus the receipt journal.

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:27.000
narrator: verify recomputes the chain — a non-zero exit is tamper proof.

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:36.000
narrator: act seven — interop. Stock tailscale clients pay the operator.

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:45.000
narrator: a real Tailscale CLI joins, pings, and settles on the chain.

00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:54.000
narrator: the loop closes — install, join, traffic, settlement, audit.

00:02:54.000 --> 00:03:03.000
narrator: every byte in this demo is reproducible from the source tree.

00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:12.000
narrator: OctraVPN — open source, chain-anchored, Tailscale-compatible.
